    "details": {
      "blurb": "Forsaken elf killer; Rolth's lover",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "elven",
          "necril"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 8
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> a pesh-addicted, self-destructive forsaken elf and the necromancer <strong>Rolth Lamm's</strong> lover (Gaedren's son, from the Ch.1 Dead Warrens). Sent to murder Ileosa's noble hit-list at Carowyn Manor, she slaughtered the whole party and posed 21 zombies into a 'masquerade of the dead,' then disguised every corpse as a blood-veil death with her wand of <em>sculpt corpse</em>.</p><p><strong>Tactics:</strong> a stealth-skirmisher who plays cat-and-mouse — sniping from hiding for bleeding Sneak Attacks, screaming-bolting clusters, then Vanishing room to room. She fights melee only from behind her zombies. Cornered alone, she flees to ambush again. <strong>The 'plague deaths' here are fakes</strong> (@Check[type:medicine|dc:20] or @Check[type:will|dc:11] to tell).</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
